  step 41: text differs
    oracle: "He looks at me with pity. \"I've seen it before. A young man like you — clever, removed. The kind that doesn't go to parties. Who takes himself too seriously. Who takes things too far.\"\n"
    brink:  "\"No—one will be getting a knighthood if the Germans make landfall,\" Harris answers sharply. He casts a quick eye to the door of the Hut to check the latch is still down, then continues in more of a murmur: \"Not you and not Hooper. Now answer me.\"\n"
  step 42: text differs
